race.comment: THE ADIGE (7) is coming along well and should be ready to peak third up. He stepped up quickly in trip second up at Cranbourne and boxed on well for third, beaten 4.5 lengths. He should be fitter again and the rise in trip again should suit. JUST MY LOT (13) has been in the mix without winning, the latest offering a second over 1454m at this track, beaten half a length. She maps for every chance and will take catching. PRECAMBRIAN (10) was fair on debut at Cranbourne when in the market. Expecting improvement off that. BLOOD BROTHER (8) was also even on debut in the same race and is in the mix.
